Document: WebSocketMultiplayerPeer
Path: godot/classes/class_websocketmultiplayerpeer.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring WebSocket handshake, timeouts, and buffer sizes.

Property Descriptions
handshake_headers (PackedStringArray): The extra headers to use during handshake. See WebSocketPeer.handshake_headers for more details.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedStringArray for more details.
Method: set_handshake_headers(value: PackedStringArray)
Method: get_handshake_headers() → PackedStringArray

handshake_timeout (float): The maximum time each peer can stay in a connecting state before being dropped. Default: 3.0
Method: set_handshake_timeout(value: float)
Method: get_handshake_timeout() → float

inbound_buffer_size (int): The inbound buffer size for connected peers. See WebSocketPeer.inbound_buffer_size for more details. Default: 65535
Method: set_inbound_buffer_size(value: int)
Method: get_inbound_buffer_size() → int

max_queued_packets (int): The maximum number of queued packets for connected peers. See WebSocketPeer.max_queued_packets for more details. Default: 4096
Method: set_max_queued_packets(value: int)
Method: get_max_queued_packets() → int

outbound_buffer_size (int): The outbound buffer size for connected peers. See WebSocketPeer.outbound_buffer_size for more details. Default: 65535
Method: set_outbound_buffer_size(value: int)
Method: get_outbound_buffer_size() → int

supported_protocols (PackedStringArray): The supported WebSocket sub-protocols. See WebSocketPeer.supported_protocols for more details.
Note: The returned array is copied and any changes to it will not update the original property value. See PackedStringArray for more details.
Method: set_supported_protocols(value: PackedStringArray)
Method: get_supported_protocols() → PackedStringArray
